Rule of 72
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
A very simple rule, which takes a time period, taking a number 72, which
 is divided by rate of growth.
 Resulting number represents a number of periods after which your investments
 will be doubled.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
72 / 10 = 7.2, which means that with 10% annual interest rate, your initial
 investment will be doubled after 7.2 years.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
It works also inversely: 72 / 10 years = 7.2, which is interest rate that
 would be needed for your money to be doubled after 10 years.
\end_layout

