\begin_layout Itemize
Savings account is an account you can make via a bank (profit, owned by
 shareholders) or a credit union (non-profit, owned by a credit union board).
 You can put there any amount of money for a small interest rate.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
It is a deposit account held at a retail bank that pays interest (0.1% for
 example) but cannot be used directly as money in the narrow sense of a
 medium of exchange.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
These accounts let customers set aside a portion of their liquid assets
 while earning a monetary return.
